    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A variety of Prussian blue that is often mixed with barium sulfate. Brunswick blue is not used in artist's paints.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
